<DOC><DOCNO> AP891023-0183 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-10-23-89 2154EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r w AM-BRF--InfantAbducted     10-23 0164</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Infant Abducted,160</SECOND><HEAD>Newborn Kidnapped From Washington Hospital</HEAD><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   An 18-day-old infant awaiting adoption wasabducted from D.C. General Hospital Monday by a woman who posed asa volunteer to the obstetrics ward, officials said.   The kidnapping happened around lunchtime.   ``At that hour of the day, mothers are coming in to feed theirbabies ... babies who are at the hospital,'' said hospitalspokeswoman Ann Chisholm. ``There is a lot of activity at that time(and) this person supposedly posed as a volunteer.''   The black male infant weighs six pounds, 10 ounces and is 19inches long, hospital officials said. He was wrapped in a yellowblanket and was wearing a newborn identification bracelet datedOct. 6.   The woman authorities believe abducted the baby was described asa black woman in her 20s, weighing between 230 pounds and 250pounds with shoulder-length cornrows.   ``We have no idea at this point'' who the woman is that took theinfant, Ms. Chisolm said.</TEXT></DOC>